company.
Burlington Industries is the latest in a long line of highly-leveraged
companies - including the likes of RJR Nabisco and Duracell - to take
advantage of record stock market levels to pay down debt via equity issues.
Interest charges on the heavy debts resulting from the Morgan Stanley-led
buy-out have compounded operating losses at the textile company for much of
the LBO period, although the operational side has improved recently.
In the year to end-September, earnings before interest and tax were Dollars
156.8m, but were offset by a Dollars 251.7m interest charge.
