THE LATEST report of the Advertising Standards Authority, published
yesterday, found particular cause for complaint with the motor industry.
The authority upheld complaints received in November against Citroen UK for
inaccurately suggesting the superiority of some aspects of a Citroen
1.4-litre Avantage to a Ford Escort 1.4LX.
Complaints were upheld against Peugeot Talbot for a claim concerning the
