engines fitted with catalytic converters, and against Seat UK for a
newspaper advertisement that combined a slogan featuring a car costing
Pounds 5,444 with a photograph showing a model costing Pounds 8,099.
Complaints against BT, Thomas Cook/P&amp;O European Ferries, the Royal Mint and
Cardiff Development Corporation - which ran a poster campaign featuring
architectural improvements to the Cardiff Bay area that had not yet been
built - were also upheld.
