FT  22 JAN 92 / Multi-party state likely in Tanzania
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DAR ES SALAAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
LEADERS of Tanzania's ruling Revolutionary Party have backed a proposal to
introduce a multi-party system, according to the state-owned Daily News,
Reuter reports from Dar es Salaam.
The party would officially endorse the switch to pluralism at a special
conference on February 18, said a statement issued by the 117-strong
executive committee in the inland capital of Dodoma late on Monday. 'We
agree with one voice to present to the national conference the proposal
 .that a multi-party system should be established in Tanzania.'
The announcement came at the end of a four-day party meeting to discuss a
report ordered by President Ali Hassan Mwinyi 10 months ago on whether to
end 30 years of one-party rule.
Mr Mwinyi is thought likely to call elections later this year after
pluralism was officially approved by early March.
