<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JAN 92 / UK Company News: UniChem buys six more pharmacies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UniChem, the pharmaceutical wholesaler, has acquired six pharmacies,
primarily in North Wales.
The combined consideration was Pounds 2.05m for goodwill. Annual turnover of
the shops totalled Pounds 3.2m.
Mr Peter Dodd, chief executive, said the recent rights issue had provided
the company with the cash resources to take advantage of lower prices
available in the retail pharmacy market.
UniChem has acquired 136 shops (including the 92 outlet chain of E Moss)
since it started to purchase pharmacies in March 1991.
