<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JAN 92 / UK Company News: Intercare trebles to more than Pounds 1.5m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Intercare Group, a supplier of healthcare products, more than doubled
turnover and trebled pre-tax profit in the year to end-October.
There was strong organic growth and all divisions - including dental,
optical, mobility and specialist pharmaceutical - continued to trade
profitably. The result included a six months' contribution from Booster
Electric Vehicles and two months' from Montis Medical.
Turnover rose to Pounds 14.9m (Pounds 6.78m) and profit to Pounds 1.52m
(Pounds 504,000). Earnings per share worked through at 7.5p on significantly
higher capital (4.1p) and a final divided of 1.5p makes the total of 2p
(1.25p).
Mr Peter Cowan, chairman, said the most significant event of the year was
the acquisition of Booster and 75 per cent of Montis, which distributes
healthcare products - including the electric vehicles assembled by Booster -
primarily in the Netherlands.
'We have been very pleased with their performance since joining the group',
Mr Cowan told shareholders.
The group had entered the current year in 'a very positive manner'. The UK
side was showing good organic growth and there were 'exciting' European
operations through Montis. Net cash at October 31 was Pounds 2.23m, against
an overdraft of Pounds 750,000 the year before.
</TEXT>
