FT  21 JAN 92 / Photograph cheque-card scheme expanded
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BARCHARD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ROYAL BANK of Scotland is to offer a further 70,000 customers the
opportunity to have their photographs on their cheque-guarantee cards.
The scheme, which is free to customers during the pilot stage, was launched
in October for branch customers in Edinburgh, Glasgow, London and
Manchester.
So far more than 8,000 customers have applied for the photograph cards. The
bank says that some people have opened accounts with the bank in order to
obtain a card with their photograph on.
Other banks have held out against introducing photograph cards, saying they
would not be effective against card fraud, and that there would be practical
problems in photographing millions of customers and ensuring that the
picture was up to date.
Mr Kenneth Baker, home secretary, is due to meet clearing banks in March to
discuss combating card fraud, including the possible introduction of
photographs.
