<TEXT>
MR RICHARD OUTHWAITE, the Lloyd's underwriter at the centre of the biggest
civil action in the history of the London insurance market, could not have
foreseen the scale of potential asbestos claims when he underwrote a number
of loss-making contracts in 1982, the High Court was told yesterday by
another prominent underwriter.
