<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JAN 92 / Appointments: Lease-back
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
One might have thought that the former staff of British &amp; Commonwealth
Merchant Bank, which was dragged down by problems at Atlantic Computers, the
computer- leasing operation that also belonged to the B &amp; C group, would
wish to have nothing further to do with the subject of leasing.
However, David Milne, who was director of capital markets at the merchant
bank until its demise last August, has moved to Baltic, the Mayfair-based
leasing and finance house. Milne, who is 39, says Baltic is a
'conservatively-run leasing company that is at the same time very
entrepreneurial'.
Sounding predictably jaundiced about the Square Mile - 'a very
inward-looking place these days' - he says he has been hired by Baltic to
build up its structured finance side. He had been with B &amp; C MB from its
inception, 'a great opportunity that foundered due to a sick parent'. Not
afflicted with false modesty, he adds: 'The fact that 80 per cent of the
former employees of (B&amp;C merchant bank) have now got good jobs is a
reflection of the calibre of those people.'
*****
Hugh Dumas and Chris Mason are directors of CREDIT LYONNAIS ROUSE.
*****
David Brennan, Richard Chenevix-Trench and Kevin Lee are directors of BARING
ASSET MANAGEMENT. John Bolsover, chief executive officer and chief
investment officer of Baring Asset Management, has become chairman of BARING
FUND MANAGERS and Kate Woollett md.
