<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JAN 92 / Appointments: Fraser leaves Whitbread for Shepherd Neame
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Angus Fraser, recently chairman of Whitbread's Thresher off-licence chain
and the group's hotels, is to join Shepherd Neame, the independent Kent
brewer, as a non-executive director and board consultant.
He will advise the company, which has been expanding rapidly and now has 315
pubs in the south-east, on the development of its retail activities and
staff training.
Fraser, 52, a former chairman of the Brewers' Society retail committee, is
leaving Whitbread in March after eight years with the brewing and retailing
group. He said yesterday that he would be pursuing a range of other
activities.
He joined Whitbread in 1984 as managing director of Whitbread Inns after 15
years with Watneys where he became deputy managing director of the Chef &amp;
Brewer.
Before entering brewing, Fraser was in the Queen's Royal Irish Hussars for
nine years; he is on the board of the Bedfordshire Tec.
